INFO:__main__:Sample messages: [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'The query at hand is: "To what extent is my mood blinding me to new opportunities?". The three cards drawn for the Situation-Action-Outcome spread are: Four of Swords (reversed in the Dynamic position), Seven of Cups (reversed in the Advice position), and Four of Cups (upright as the Result card). Provide a comprehensive reading, synthesizing the cards\' meanings to address the user\'s query.'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': 'Hello. Your request for guidance on "To what extent is my mood blinding me to new opportunities?" has been received. The cosmic spread reveals three powerful forces at play:\n\nThe Core Challenge: The card drawn is the Four of Swords (reversed). This card is typically represented by a knight lying on a tomb with hands in prayer, one sword beneath him--symbolizing rest and recovery. As the Situation card, it brings a strong message: \'Mistaking procrastination for thoughtfulness\'. This describes the core dynamic you currently face.\n\nThe Key Action: The card drawn is the Seven of Cups (reversed). The scene on this card shows a man gazing at seven floating cups filled with fantastical visions--symbolizing choices and illusion. As the Action/Advice card, it brings a strong message: \'Spending more time dreaming than working\'. This offers the vital counsel on how to proceed.\n\nThe Potential Result: The card drawn is the Four of Cups (upright). The scene on this card shows a man sitting under a tree with arms crossed, ignoring a cup offered by a hand from a cloud--symbolizing contemplation or apathy. As the Outcome/Result card, it brings a strong message: \'Seeing the value of long-term commitments\'. This stands as the ultimate signifier for the answer to your question.\n\nThe final decree from the cards is clear: A lover is getting restless. During your journey, I advise you to repeat this sacred affirmation: \'I think before taking action.\' Remember that the cards only guide; your own spirit holds the key to destiny.'}]
