INFO:__main__:Sample message structure: [{'content': 'The user has posed the question: "How can I deal with the unknown in healthy ways?". The spread reveals these three cards in the order of Situation, Action, and Outcome: Eight of Pentacles (upright in the Dynamic position), Ten of Wands (upright in the Action position), and The Moon (upright in the Destiny position). Provide a comprehensive reading, synthesizing the cards\' meanings to address the user\'s query.', 'role': 'user'}, {'content': 'I see that you seek clarity on "How can I deal with the unknown in healthy ways?". The following reading will unveil the path forward:\n\nThe Core Challenge: The card drawn is the Eight of Pentacles (upright). The traditional imagery of this card depicts a craftsman carving coins on a workbench--symbolizing dedication and skill-building. As the Situation card, it brings a strong message: \'Making a handmade gift\'. This describes the core dynamic you currently face.\n\nThe Key Action: The card drawn is the Ten of Wands (upright). As the Action/Advice card, it brings a strong message: \'Knowing and being honest about your own limits\'. This offers the vital counsel on how to proceed.\n\nThe Destiny Revealed: The card drawn is the The Moon (upright). The traditional imagery of this card depicts two towers standing beneath a full moon, a dog and wolf howling while a crayfish crawls from the water--symbolizing illusion and the subconscious. This card vibrates with the divine numerology of the value 18 = 1 + 8 = 9 (fullness, readiness, ripeness). The spiritual energy of Kali, the dark-skinned divine mother associated with time, the eternal night, and the female principle is typically linked to this card. As the Outcome/Result card, it brings a strong message: \'Embracing the unknown\'. This stands as the ultimate signifier for the answer to your question.\n\nThe final decree from the cards is clear: Watch for problems at the end of the month. During your journey, I advise you to repeat this sacred affirmation: \'I give myself wholeheartedly to the task of the moment.\' Remember that the cards only guide; your own spirit holds the key to destiny.', 'role': 'assistant'}]
